Activity: A24 - Teach your family about a cybersecurity topic

Objective
The goal of this activity was to educate a family member about basic cybersecurity practices to improve their awareness and online safety/

Method
I explained simple cybersecurity concepts to a family member, focusing on phishing attacks and password security. i used real-life examples, such as fake messages and suspicious links, to make the explanations easier to understand.

Findings
1. The family member learned how to recognise phishing messages and avoid clicking suspicious links.
2. They understood the importance of using strong and unique passwords.
3. They became more cautious about sharing personal information online.

Security Principle
This activity supports ocnfidentiality and integrity by helping prevent unauthorised access to personal information and reducing the risk of scams.

Reflection
This activity showed that many people are not fully aware of common cybersecurity threats. teaching basic concepts can significantly improve everyday security and reduce the risk of attacks.
